{"lemma": "أَمْسٌ", "slug": "أَمْسٌ", "root": "#.م.س", "root_slug": "_-م-س", "root_link": "/words/roots/_-م-س", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "أَمْس", "root": "", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 4}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n1244"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "yesterday", "fa": "دیروز", "ur": "گزشتہ کل", "tr": "dün", "id": "kemarin", "bn": "গতকাল", "es": "ayer", "fr": "hier", "de": "gestern", "ru": "вчера", "zh": "昨天"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of أَمْس (ʔams)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n1244", "headword_ar": "اـَمْس", "root": "Ams", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Yesterday,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the day before the present day"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by one night,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,) and tropically applied to (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is before that,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a short time before,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd in x. 25,) [used as a subst. and as an adv.,] is indecl., with any of the three vowels for its termination: (K:) [written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosi", "text_ar": "اَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^mosa", "text_ar": "امْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^mosu", "text_ar": "امْسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] or it is an adv. n., indecl., with kesr for its termination, unless made indeterminate, or made determinate [be the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and sometimes indecl. with fet-h: (EzZejjájee, M, TA:) or, accord. to I Hsh, the termination with fet-h is a rejected form; and that with damm is not mentioned by any of the grammarians: (TA:) but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu*o A^amosa", "text_ar": "مُذْ اَمْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Since yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] occurs, used by poetic licence: (Sb, S:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amos", "text_ar": "اَمْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a noun of which the last letter is made movent to avoid the concurrence of two quiescent letters: and the Arabs differ respecting it: (S:) most of them make it indecl., with kesr for its termination, when it is determinate [without the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but some of them make it [imperfectly] decl. when it is determinate [in the same manner]: (S, K: *) [accord. to the most approved usage,] you say, ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotuhu A^amosi", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُهُ اَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAlA^amosi", "text_ar": "بِالاَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is more common, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosa", "text_ar": "الاَمْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I saw him yesterday;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA raA^ayotuhu mu*oA^amosi", "text_ar": "مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْاَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have not seen him since yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and if you have not seen him [since the day next] before that, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA raA^ayotuhu mu*o A^aw~alu", "text_ar": "مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ اَوَّلُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino A^amosi", "text_ar": "مِنْ اَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have not seen him since the day before yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and if you have not seen him [since] two days before that, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA raA^ayotuhu mu*o", "text_ar": "مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aw~alu mino A^aw~ala mino A^amosi", "text_ar": "اَوَّلُ مِنْ اَوَّلَ مِنْ اَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have not seen him since the day before the day before yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (ISk, TA.) The phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotuhu A^amosK", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُهُ اَمْسٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I saw him yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] has also been heard, but it is extr. (K.) The people of El-Hijáz make"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amos", "text_ar": "اَمْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "indecl., with kesr for its termination; and the Benoo-Temeem do the same when it is in the accus. or gen. case; but these latter make it [imperfectly] decl. when it is in the nom. case, saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ahaba A^amosu bimaA fiyhi", "text_ar": "ذَهَبَ اَمْسُ بِمَا فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Yesterday has gone with what"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "happened"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "during it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; whereas the people of El-Hijáz say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ahaba", "text_ar": "ذَهَبَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosi bimaA fiyhi", "text_ar": "اَمْسِ بِمَا فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", because it is [held by them to be] indecl. on account of its implying that it has the determinative article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[understood as prefixed to it], the kesreh being added to avoid the concurrence of two quiescent letters; while the Benoo-Temeem hold it to be, in the nom. case, a deviation from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_amosu", "text_ar": "الاـَمْسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and therefore imperfectly decl., because of its being determinate, [and so resembling a proper name,] and its deviation from the original form, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saHaru", "text_ar": "سَحَرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the like case: (IB, TA:) all of the Arabs, however, make it decl. when the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is prefixed to it, (S, K, *) and when it is made indeterminate, or is prefixed to another noun: (S:) they say, using it indeterminately,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~u gadK SaAy^irN A^amosKA", "text_ar": "كُلُّ غَدٍ صَايِرٌ اَمْسٍا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Every morrow becomes a yesterday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, * IB;) and making it determinate by the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", they say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAna", "text_ar": "كَانَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosu Tay~ibFA", "text_ar": "الاَمْسُ طَيِّبًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The yesterday was good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (IB,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maDay AlA^amosu AlmubaAraku", "text_ar": "مَضَي الاَمْسُ المُبَارَكُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The blessed yesterday has past"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S;) and prefixing it to another noun,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~u A^amosinaA kaAna Tay~ibFA", "text_ar": "كُلُّ اَمْسِنَا كَانَ طَيِّبًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "All of our yesterday was good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (IB,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maDaY A^amosunaA", "text_ar": "مَضَى اَمْسُنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Our yesterday has past"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) [therefore,] in the following verse,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "waA_in~iY waqafotu Alyawoma waAlA^amosi qabolahu\n                      \n                     \n                        bibaAbika Hat~aY kaAdati Al$~amosu tagorubu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And verily I stood to-day, and yesterday before it, at thy door until the sun was almost setting"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (thus related by IAar in two different ways,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosi", "text_ar": "الاَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosa", "text_ar": "الاَمْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosi", "text_ar": "الاَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is redundant, because it is implied in the word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosi", "text_ar": "اَمْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amosa", "text_ar": "الاَمْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is not implied in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosa", "text_ar": "اَمْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and therefore is prefixed to make it determinate. (IJ, M.) The pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=musN", "text_ar": "ا=مُسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=maAsN", "text_ar": "ا=مَاسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Zj, K,) both pls. of pauc., (Zj, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^muwsN", "text_ar": "امُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Zj, K, TA, [in the CK, incorrectly,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AmuwosN", "text_ar": "امُوْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) which is a pl. of mult. (Zj, TA.) There is no dim. form of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amos", "text_ar": "اَمْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; like as there is none of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gadN", "text_ar": "غَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaAriHapu", "text_ar": "البَارِحَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kayofa", "text_ar": "كَيْفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ayona", "text_ar": "اَيْنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mataY", "text_ar": "مَتَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aY~u", "text_ar": "اَىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Einda", "text_ar": "عِندَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the names of the months and those of the days of the week, except"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljumoEapu", "text_ar": "الجُمْعَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Sb, S.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "TA", "Sb", "S", "IB", "Zj"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}